Introduction: The pressure of prevention and control of epidemic situation at the grass-roots level mainly includes weak consciousness of protection of residents, lack of medical staff and shortage of protective equipment.

By Wu Mianqiang

A result of Hubei many places "closed city" pneumonia epidemic, affected the rural areas around Wuhan grass-roots People's New Year atmosphere.

Compared with past years when people busily pasted couplets, put up New Year pictures, hung lanterns, and heard the sound of firecrackers one after another, this New Year in these villages and towns, roads were closed everywhere, every household closed its doors tightly, and villagers did not leave their homes, designed to stop the sadistic spread of pneumonia.

Compared with the severe situation of epidemic prevention and control in Wuhan City, township and rural grass-roots units are also the first line of defense.

Over the past few days, reporters have visited towns and villages around Wuhan and found that there are shortcomings in the prevention and control situation at the grass-roots level. According to the reporter's investigation, the pressure of prevention and control of epidemic situation at the grass-roots level mainly includes the weak consciousness of protection of residents, the shortage of medical staff and protective equipment at the grass-roots level, etc. .

"The heat alone is too much for the hands. "

The outbreak spread to the Wuhan suburb of Florida, Xinzhou, after the city was declared closed on January 23. This is the municipal district of Northeast Wuhan, Huanggang City Tuanfeng County East, West Wuhan Huangpi District District, South and Wuhan Hongshan district, Ezhou Huarong District across the river.

"If we find people coming back from Wuhan, we have to go into their homes and check if they have a fever, if their temperature is normal, and we have to report them every day. These days, they are 'ok, ' and there are no cases of fever, fever or (suspected coronavirus pneumonia) , " Liu Ming, the Party secretary of a village under the Xinzhou City Street office, told reporters.

The reporter noted that Liu Ming's region of Xinzhou lies right between the Wuhan and Huanggang, where the outbreak is more severe. Xinzhou District has been awarded the title of "Home of Chinese architecture" by the China Construction Association, with one hundred thousand people in the region working in the construction industry in Wuhan and across the country.

There are more than ten communities and dozens of administrative villages under the jurisdiction of the district office of this city, and there are a large number of migrant workers in Wuhan and even in the whole country. The grassroots effort to prevent new coronavirus pneumonia has put pressure on Liu Ming and his colleagues.

"We called the village captains in advance on December twenty-nine, " Liu Ming told reporters. "Don't drop in on each other during the Spring Festival. ". In fact, in the grass-roots township, village epidemic prevention and control, the villagers group leader is often the most front-line screening staff, group leaders know the situation of each household, easy to feel row.

According to our reporter's understanding, there are three special fever clinics in Xinzhou District, but there are no such specialized clinics in the villages under the jurisdiction of the People's governments, nor are there sufficient technical means to screen and treat patients with fever, group leaders need to constantly in the villagers wechat group exhorted "if there is a fever in the near future, general fatigue, respiratory symptoms such as dry cough or dyspnea please feel free to check and see a doctor. ".

"Now patients with fever have to be transferred to Xinzhou District People's Hospital and Xinzhou District hospital for blood tests, " said Liu Ming, who said several people in the village were found to have fever when they went to the village clinic to buy medicine, they were then sent to the district of Xinzhou for testing and, in the event that they were not infected, they were told to isolate themselves at home and to keep away from their families and outsiders.

Liu Ming told reporters that there were about 3,000 villagers in the village. Out of proportion to the tremendous pressure of epidemic prevention, there is only one village clinic in the whole village and only 2 medical staff in the clinic. Ordinary villagers go to this clinic to see a doctor and buy medicine.

For example, in the work of temperature measurement for the entire village, the village doctor of the clinic clearly told the reporter that he could not go door-to-door every day to check the temperature of the villagers. "This is also not realistic, there is not enough manpower, and there is a lack of protective equipment. "

To be sure, small medical thermometers are impractical in a natural village of 3,000 or so people. According to the introduction of a village cadre, Each Person Measures 5 minutes, every morning and evening a total of 2 times, "this workload is too big, light body temperature people busy. "

We're running low on protective gear

The same problem occurred in a town in eastern Hubei, where Li Bo, a town cadre, told reporters that there were also problems in the coverage of body temperature tests in the local area. They were waiting for the higher authorities to transfer equipment such as infrared body temperature monitors.

"The biggest fear now is that some villagers themselves will hide cases of fever, fever and suspected coronavirus pneumonia from going to the clinic, " Liu Ming told reporters, it's hard for them to know right away and solve the problem.

"In the aspect of epidemic prevention, everyone should wear face masks, but the villagers' awareness of protection is still relatively weak, which has great disadvantages, " Dr. Cheng told reporters. In the view of many village cadres, want to transfer to the infrared body temperature detector is "extravagant hope" , the most basic protective masks are in short supply.

Dr. Cheng said his clinic has been short of masks, the N95 mask and general medical surgical masks. "The day before yesterday, every household in the village only issued a dozen or so general surgical masks. Strictly speaking, the average family of four or five did not have enough for one day. "

Liu Ming also told reporters, "according to the population of the village, the daily use of ordinary masks around 6,000, but only a few days ago to 2,000 masks. "

On Jan. 27, the town where Li Bo lived finally got a mask from above. But the whole town dozens of natural villages, each village only issued more than 100 masks. "This batch of masks should only be used by village cadres when they go on patrol, " Li said.

In the epidemic prevention and control, in fact, the need to spray disinfectant in and outside the village, for the disinfection of densely populated places. But the job just doesn't seem to be done. "hand-washing, disinfection measures to keep up with the more difficult. " Dr. Cheng told reporters, now everywhere road closure, purchase extremely inconvenient, but also to wait until the above assistance.

In addition to these protection shortages, the shortage of ambulances has also made it difficult to transfer suspected new coronavirus pneumonia patients. Gao Xinwu, director of the hospital in the city of Xinzhou District, told reporters that when highly suspected patients are encountered, they undergo centralized transfer and a local quarantine station has been set up.

"during the transfer of patients to the isolation station, our staff can only use their own cars, " Gao said. Gao Xinwu said that the area is now closed to traffic and it is difficult to find a suitable transport vehicle, even if it is found, no one would pay for a car to transport it.

"Our medical section chief, Li Jun, had to wear protective equipment and moved several batches, " Gao said. In the picture sent by Gao Xinwu, the reporter saw that Li Jun was driving a motor vehicle in a protective suit.

The hardest thing to control is people

"people from other places want to come back, migrant workers want to go back home, and people's awareness of prevention is still relatively poor, " Li Bo, a township official in eastern Hubei, told reporters on Jan. 26, the second day of the Lunar New Year, as he was still working on the front line of Disease Prevention and control.

Li's district is more than 200 kilometers from the epicenter of the outbreak, Wuhan, and a three-or four-hour drive away. Under Wuhan's severe epidemic situation, the local prevention and control situation can not be underestimated. During the Spring Festival holiday, Li Bo worked overtime at the township government, and their entire township staff was also on duty during this period.

Every day, Li Bo collated statistics on the town's prevention and control work situation, as well as the "close contacts" observation and statistics of the overall situation of returnees, timely reporting to the county.

As Wuhan's order to seal off the city was issued, the surrounding area followed suit. It often takes a while for disease control directives to travel from the province to the towns and villages of Wuhan and surrounding cities.

According to the reporter, Hubei Township Epidemic Prevention and control work, the real start about January 23, that is, the lunar month twenty-nine.

Li's town, in the remote heart of Dabie Mountains, has more migrant workers in the countryside. The days leading up to New Year's Eve are the peak for returning home, with many migrant workers heading home directly or via Wuhan. On December twenty-nine, the local new coronavirus epidemic prevention and Control Headquarters has issued orders, all routes of passenger transport, buses, taxis stopped operating.

Returning from Wuhan, the village cadres have become the "work object" of this Spring Festival.

"The biggest pressure now is to prevent and control the flow of people. Migrant workers returning to the village want to escape. " And those left behind in Wuhan have recently also sneaked back to the village. A local township official told reporters.

There is a local family of 3 people, returned home from Wuhan, was found by neighbors hence to the village report. "The person in charge of prevention and control in the town got the news and immediately went to the House with the village cadres and isolated them at home, " the township official told reporters that no problems had been found.

In addition to migrant workers, the local customs "difficult to overcome" is placed in the grass-roots epidemic prevention and control cadres in front of a difficult problem. Now is the Spring Festival, the villagers inevitably to New Year, party. According to the reporter, the Spring Festival Mutual New Year is the custom of the local rural people, the general younger generation to go to the elder family New Year.

"No assemblies of any kind are allowed, no one is allowed to go around each other or pay New Year calls, and everyone wears a mask when they go out. Those who do not believe rumors or spread rumors are dealt with by the competent administrative departments according to law, " said the notice issued by the local headquarters.

Nevertheless, some villagers are going to pay New Year calls. According to our reporter's understanding, although the eastern Hubei region has issued specific circulars on the control of floating people and traffic control in counties and towns, one by one they have issued to the natural villages under their jurisdiction, and some village cadres have made extensive publicity, "But there are still some villagers who don't know each other well enough, and the phenomenon of relatives visiting each other to greet the New Year also exists. "

There are also difficulties in preventing and controlling vehicles traveling everywhere. Several checkpoints have been set up from Li Bo's county to towns to control the flow of personnel. "But some residents are not moving according to the requirements, and there is still some pressure on the control of personnel. "

In this regard, in order to prevent villagers from paying New Year greetings to each other, village cadres or village volunteers in local villages and towns will go to each village every day to spread propaganda in the form of big speakers and percussion gongs, 24 hours a day, request "do not visit new year, with mobile phone New Year. "

The reporter visited the rural area of Xinzhou district in the far city of Wuhan and found that the village had sent the notice to the group leaders, who informed each household one by one, "not allowed to go out New Year, stay at home. "

(at the request of the interviewee, Liu Ming, Li Bo and Liu Shigao were given pseudonyms.)
